#-        Barren Arrakis§0
§0
§0Cyrus, governor of§0
§0Arrakis, announced on§0
§0the 19th of April that§0
§0harvesting sand in§0
§0Arrakis is an offense§0
§0punishable by law.§0
§0Governor Cyrus has§0
§0stated that anyone§0
§0caught breaking this§0
§0new law will be§0
§0charged with griefing.§0

#- In addition to this new§0
§0law change in Arrakis,§0
§0Governor Cyrus has§0
§0proposed his new plan,§0
§0titled, "Make Arrakis§0
§0Great Again", to§0
§0restore Arrakis's§0
§0landscape. This plan's§0
§0motive is to smooth§0
§0Arrakis's landscape§0
§0from the excess of§0
§0sand farming, and to...§0

#- restore the sand to§0
§0important areas.§0
§0Governor Cyrus is§0
§0accepting any§0
§0donations and help the§0
§0citizens and residents§0
§0of Aquila are willing to§0
§0give.§0
§0
§0Aquilan citizens may§0
§0harvest sand to the§0
§0south of Aquila now, in§0
§0the ocean.§0

#-   "Micro-Aggressions"§0
§0
§0On the night of April§0
§018th, controversy§0
§0sparked as§0
§0SpiritThrasher, a new§0
§0Aquilan resident, was§0
§0caught mining around§0
§0Microdose's bunker.§0
§0SpiritThrasher pleads§0
§0innocence on his part,§0
§0claiming he got lost in§0
§0the tunnels
#- beneath...§0

#- Aquila's surface, and§0
§0was simply attempting§0
§0to mine his way back§0
§0out when he ran into§0
§0Microdose's bunker.§0
§0
§0Microdose does not§0
§0plan on pushing§0
§0charges.§0

#-    "Scholar Scrawler"§0
§0
§0On April 15th, Chief§0
§0Justice Gjum§0
§0announced the§0
§0creation of the§0
§0Scholar's Guild. Led by§0
§0Inferior Justice§0
§0Cyrus, the Scholar's§0
§0Guild's  purpose is to§0
§0educate and entertain§0
§0Aquila's citizens.§0
§0Members of the§0

#- Scholar's Guild...
#- write works of fiction§0
§0and non-fiction, to§0
§0contribute to the§0
§0nation's culture and§0
§0knowledge.§0
§0
§0The Scholar's Guild§0
§0has picked up the§0
§0Aquilan newspaper, as§0
§0well. The previous§0
§0owner of the Aquilan§0
§0Times has not been§0
§0heard from for quite a§0

#- period of...§0

